Fig. 
6

), considerably projecting beyond lower jaw, wider than long (SL/EE 
0.77
); canthus rostralis distinct, moderately sharp, almost straight-lined from eye to just beyond nostril, slightly convex near tip of snout; loreal region almost vertical, slightly concave; nostril directed dorsolaterally; situated much closer to tip of snout than to eye (EN/NS 
1.42
), separated from each other by distance greater than distance between eye and nostril (NN/EN 
1.13
); eyes directed anterolaterally, moderately protruding, relatively small (ED/HL 
0.31
); eye diameter shorter than snout (ED/SL 
0.70
); interorbital distance much wider than upper eyelid (IO/EW 
1.71
